./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:1:#**************************************************************************
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:2:#                      Card for MadAnalysis                               *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:3:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:4:# This file is used to set the classes and options for                    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:5:# the MadAnalysis program.                                                *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:6:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:7:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:8:# Some comments about the classes                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:9:# 1. Plots are for classes of particles.                                  *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:10:# 2. Each particle is identified by its PDG code.                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:11:# 3. Classes names are arbitrary (4 symbols max, no spaces allowed).      *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:12:# 4. Particles in the same class will be ordered with the 'ordering       *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:13:#    function' in the file in_func.f.                                     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:14:# 5. Classes can be added/edited/removed at will, and given a name        *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:15:#    that will then appear in the plots.                                  *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:16:# 6. A particle can be put in one class only. Putting a particle in       *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:17:#    two or more classes can lead to double counting of events.           *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:18:# 7. The class name mET is missing Energy and its name is reserved.       *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:19:#    If used, it must be put last in the classes list below.              *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:20:# 8. If events contain particles not belonging to an existing class,      *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:21:#    a new class will automatically be generated.                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:22:# 9. For LHCO events the PDG code 21 is assigned to a jet (not            *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:23:#    b-tagged), 5 to a b-tagged jet and 12 to missing ET.                 *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:24:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:25:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:26:# Some comments about the cuts                                            *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:27:# 1. In the file kin_func.f the functions on which cuts can be applied    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:28:#    are given.                                                           *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:29:# 2. The syntax is as follows.                                            *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:30:#      etmin 1 3 30d0                                                     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:31:#     means that from the first class the Et of the first three particles *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:32:#     has to be greater than 30 GeV.                                      *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:33:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:34:#      etmissmin 20d0                                                     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:35:#     means that there must be at least 20 GeV of missing Et              *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:36:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:37:#      dRmin 2 1 4 3 3d0                                                  *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:38:#     means that the distance between the first particle in the second    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:39:#     class and the first three particles in the fourth class has to be   *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:40:#     greater than 3.                                                     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:41:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:42:#      ptmax 1 3 10d0                                                     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:43:#      ptmax 1 2 15d0                                                     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:44:#     means that the maximum pt of the third particle in the first class  *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:45:#     has to smaller than 10 GeV, and the first two particles of this     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:46:#     class has to be smaller than 15 GeV                                 *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:47:# 3. The ordering of the particles within a class can be set with the     *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:48:#    'ordering function' in the file kin_func.f.                          *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:49:# 4. For all the 'min' cuts, an event will be thrown away if the particle *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:50:#    does not exist. On the other hand, for all the 'max' cuts the cut    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:51:#    will be ignored if the particle does not exist                       *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:52:#    (Only dRij is an exception, for which it is the other way around)    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:53:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:54:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:55:#                                                                         *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:56:# Some comments about the plotting options                                *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:57:# 1. In the file kin_func.f the functions can be found that can be        *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:58:#    plotted. (only for off-line usage)                                   *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:59:# 2. With the plotting options one can set the number of plots for each   *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:60:#    of these functions.                                                  *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:61:# 3. One has to specify for each variable which particles from which      *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:62:#    class are used to set the plots. Syntax:                             *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:63:#    	et  2 4                                                           *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:64:#    means that the transverse energy of the first four particles in the  *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:65:#    second class will be plotted.                                        *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:66:#       mij 1 3                                                           *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:67:#	mij 2 2                                                           *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:68:#    means that for the invariant mass plots the first three particles    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:69:#    from the first class and the first two from the second class will be *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/plot_card_default.dat:70:#    used to plot the invariant mass of two particles. (10 plots)         *

./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:2:#                          Reweight Module                               *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:3:#                Matrix-Element reweighting at LO/NLO                    *
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:4:#  Mattelaer Olivier                                    arxiv:1607.00763 *  
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:5:#*************************************************************************
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:6:#          
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:7:# Note: 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:8:#   1) the value of alpha_s will be used from the event so the value in
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:9:#      the param_card is not taken into account.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:10:#   2) It is (in general) dangerous/wrong to change parameters by a large
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:11:#      amount, if this changes the shape of the matrix elements a lot.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:12:#      (For example, changing a particle's mass by much more than its
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:13:#      width leads to very inaccurate result). In such a case, separate 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:14:#      event generation runs are needed.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:15:#
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:16:#************************************************************************
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:17:# ENTER YOUR COMMANDS BELOW. 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:18:#************************************************************************
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:20:change mode NLO    # Define type of Reweighting. For LO sample this command
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:21:                   # has no effect since only "LO" mode is allowed.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:23:#uncomment if you do not want to overwrite the reweight file of Sudakov in rw_me
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:24:#change rwgt_dir /PATH_MG5_BRANCH/NAME_FOLDER
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:26:#uncomment if you want to use Sudakov Reweight
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:27:#change include_sudakov True
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:32:#  SPECIFY A PATH OR USE THE SET COMMAND LIKE THIS:
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:33:# set sminputs 1 130 # modify 1/alpha_EW
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:37:#************************************************************************
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:38:# Manual:      https://cp3.irmp.ucl.ac.be/projects/madgraph/wiki/Reweight
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:39:#************************************************************************
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:40:#
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:41:# Example of (standard) code for the computation of two weights:
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:42:#
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:43:# launch                    ! tag to start the computation of the first weight
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:44:#  set BLOCKNAME ID VALUE   ! rule to modify the current param_card
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:45:#  set BLOCKNAME ID VALUE   ! rule to modify the current param_card
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:46:# launch                    ! start to compute a second weight
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:47:#  /home/Cards/param_card_2.dat ! you can also enter a path to a valid card
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:48:#
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:49:# Note: The command to specify the parameter are AFTER the associated "launch" 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:50:#
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:51:# Possible options: 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:52:#   You can enter one of the following lines to customize the reweighting 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:53:#   procedure. These need to be given before the 'launch' command.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:54:#
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:55:# change model NAME : use another model for the matrix-elements to reweight 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:56:#        with. In this case you need to provide the path to a correct 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:57:#        param_card for the new model; you cannot modify the original one 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:58:#        with the 'set' command.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:59:# change process DEF [--add]: change the process by which you reweight. 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:60:#        The initial and final state particles of the new process should 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:61:#        be exactly identical to the ones in the original process.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:62:# change helicity False: perform the reweighting by helicity summed 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:63:#        matrix-elements even if the events have been written with a 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:64:#        single helicity state.       
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:65:# change mode XXX: change the type of reweighting performed.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:66:#        allowed values: LO, NLO, LO+NLO
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:67:#        - This command has no effect for reweighting an .lhe event file with LO accuracy. 
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:68:#          In that case LO mode is always used (whatever entry is set).
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:69:#        - When the .lhe file reweighted is at NLO accuracy, then all modes are allowed.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:70:#          * "LO" is an approximate leading order method
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:71:#          * "NLO" is the NLO accurate method
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:72:#          * "LO+NLO" runs both
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:73:#       - "NLO" and "LO+NLO" modes requires 'store_rwgt_info' equals True (run_card.dat)
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:74:#          If the reweighting is done at generation level this parameter will
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:75:#          automatically be set on True.
./PROC_sm_0/Cards/reweight_card_default.dat:76:#************************************************************************
